We reduced a 1.8TB Delta MERGE from 52 minutes to 18 minutes — without increasing cluster size.

SCD Type 2.
Daily updates.
Production workload.

The bottleneck wasn’t compute.

It was data layout + execution strategy.

Here’s what was happening:

• Full-table scans during MERGE
• Excessive file rewrites
• Poor clustering on match keys
• No effective data skipping

So we changed the storage strategy — not the cluster.

1️⃣ Re-clustered data on frequently matched keys
2️⃣ Compacted files before MERGE (OPTIMIZE to control file count)
3️⃣ Aligned join conditions with partition/clustering design
4️⃣ Leveraged AQE to handle skewed updates dynamically

Impact:
• 65% faster MERGE runtime
• 30% lower compute cost
• More consistent job performance during peak ingestion

At TB scale, MERGE performance isn’t about cleaner code.

It’s about how your file layout interacts with Spark’s execution plan.

